===============================================================================
edge-func-type-dep
===============================================================================
Test that func->type_dep edges create correct dependency direction.
When function F has a type dependency on T (e.g., creates/uses T internally),
F's crate depends on T's crate.
At crate level: crate_app -> crate_types (app depends on types)

--- file: types/Cargo.toml ---
[package]
name = "types"

--- file: types/src/lib.rs ---
pub struct Config {
    pub value: u32,
}

impl Config {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Config { value: 0 }
    }
}

--- file: app/Cargo.toml ---
[package]
name = "app"

[dependencies]
types = { path = "../types" }

--- file: app/src/lib.rs ---
use types::Config;

/// Function creates and uses Config internally
pub fn initialize() {
    let config = Config::new();
    let _ = config.value;
}

